annotationA: Serpin 38F (Spn38F) is a predicted serine endopeptidase inhibitor. It is expressed in the male accessory glands and transferred to females during mating. Spn38F ectopic expression in females provides anti-microbial protection
annotationB: Accessory gland protein 53C14a, isoform A; It is involved in the biological process described with: multicellular organism reproduction
